{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001","id":"msg_01NcjduZqKrXdcbHcL4tTCbM","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user wants me to generate exactly 10 realistic fake OCR recipe text files. Let me break down the requirements:\n\n1. **File location**: `tools/title-loop/input/{RECIPE_TITLE}.generated.24.txt`\n\n2. **Filename rules**:\n   - Use SPACES, not hyphens or underscores\n   - Preserve Polish diacritics\n   - Filename title must match the main title in the text (case-insensitive OK)\n\n3. **Recipe mix**: ~60% English, ~40% Polish, variety of categories, mix of single-word and multi-word titles\n\n4. **Avoid existing recipes**: There's a long list of existing recipes I must NOT use\n\n5. **Pattern requirements**:\n   - 5 files with OCR_CORRUPTION: character misrecognition (só1 for sól, ı for l, hyphenation artifacts like 'gorg-onzol', garbage tokens)\n   - 3 files with NARRATIVE: 3-7 lines of prose cooking story before ingredient list\n   - 2 files with COMPOUND: multiple recipes in one title (e.g., \"RECIPE1 + RECIPE2\" or \"RECIPE WITH VARIATION : ALTERNATIVE\")\n\n6. **File length**: 15-60 lines, spillover should be 40-60 lines\n\nLet me create 10 unique recipes:\n1. Apple Crumble (English) - narrative version\n2. Żurek z Pieczarkami (Polish) - OCR corruption\n3. Roasted Garlic Broccoli (English) - straightforward\n4. Sernik Malinowy (Polish) - narrative version\n5. Lentil Stew (English) - OCR corruption\n6. Ciastka Miodowe (Polish) - OCR corruption\n7. Beet Salad with Walnuts (English) - compound title\n8. Pierogi Kartoflanki (Polish) - OCR corruption\n\n\n9. Creamy Mushroom Pasta (English) - compound title with variation\n10. Kompot z Malin (Polish) - narrative version\n\nI need to verify against the exclusion list to ensure none of these conflict with existing recipes, then proceed with generating the files.\n\n1. **Apple Crumble** (English) - NARRATIVE - 40 lines\n2. **Żurek z Pieczarkami** (Polish) - OCR_CORRUPTION - 35 lines\n3. **Roasted Garlic Broccoli** (English) - straightforward - 20 lines\n4. **Sernik Malinowy ze Czekoladą** (Polish) - NARRATIVE - 45 lines\n5. **Lentil and Vegetable Stew** (English) - OCR_CORRUPTION - 35 lines\n6. **Ciastka Miodowe z Cynamonem** (Polish) - OCR_CORRUPTION - 25 lines\n7. **Beet Walnut Salad + Beet and Goat Cheese Salad** (English) - COMPOUND - 50 lines\n8. **Pierogi z Kapustą i Grzybami** (Polish) - OCR_CORRUPTION - 30 lines\n9. **Creamy Mushroom Pasta** (English) - COMPOUND - 40 lines\n10. **Kompot z Malin i Czarnych Porzeczek** (Polish) - NARRATIVE - 40 lines\n\nI need to verify the exclusion list to ensure none of these overlap with restricted recipes. Checking against the provided restrictions, I notice some mushroom-based dishes are already excluded, so I should confirm my selections don't duplicate those entries. The current list appears to have good variety across both English and Polish recipes with different preparation styles and complexity levels. but Creamy Spinach Risotto is a distinct dish. I should focus on recipes that genuinely don't appear in the exclusion list. For English options, I can consider Apple Crumble, Pan Roasted Cod, Lentil and Root Vegetable Stew, Garlic Shrimp Pasta, Herb Butter Roasted Vegetables, Lemon Curd Tart, Blackberry Pie, Wild Mushroom Soup, and Smoked Salmon Bagel. On the Polish side, Żurek z Pieczarkami and Ciastka Miodowe z Cynamonem work since they're variations not explicitly listed.\n\nNow I'm selecting my final 10 recipes with specific formats and line counts: Apple Crumble as NARRATIVE (40 lines), Żurek z Pieczarkami as OCR_CORRUPTION (35 lines), Pan Roasted Cod straightforward (22 lines), Sernik Malinowy ze Czekoladą as NARRATIVE (45 lines), Lentil and Root Vegetable Stew as OCR_CORRUPTION (38 lines), Ciastka Miodowe z Cynamonem as OCR_CORRUPTION (28 lines), Beet Walnut Salad combined with Beet and Goat Cheese Salad as COMPOUND (50 lines), Pierogi z Kapustą i Grzybami as OCR_CORRUPTION (32 lines), Creamy Spinach Risotto with Garlic Variation as COMPOUND (48 lines), and Kompot z Malin i Czarnych Porzeczek as NARRATIVE (42 lines). Checking the distribution: I have 4 OCR_CORRUPTION files but need 5, so I need to adjust one recipe to fit that pattern instead. me verify the line counts add up: 40 + 35 + 25 + 45 + 38 + 28 + 50 + 32 + 48 + 42 = 383 lines total. That works within the target range. The distribution is now balanced across all three corruption types with the right proportions.\n\nNow I'm creating the actual files with realistic content. For OCR corruption, I need to incorporate specific artifacts—digit substitutions like 'só1' instead of 'sól', dotless characters, hyphenation breaks mid-word, and random garbage tokens. The narrative entries should feel personal and reflective, while compound recipes need clear structure with multiple variations. Starting with the first file, an Apple Crumble narrative that opens with a nostalgic memory of autumn afternoons in a grandmother's kitchen, describing how the buttery topping complements spiced apples. żur starter culture, mushrooms sautéed until tender, bacon crisped, onions and garlic softened together. Potatoes cut into cubes, seasoned with salt and pepper, finished with a touch of mustard powder. The method begins by melting butter in a large pot, browning the bacon, then adding aromatics before incorporating the remaining components. yka białego wina, sok z cytryny, sól i pieprz. Przygotować 200 g młodych szparagów i 4 pomidory czereśniowe.\n\nRozgrzać patelnię, doprawić filety dorsza i smażyć po 3-4 minuty z każdej strony. Dodać masło, wino i cytrynę, następnie gotować szparagi z pomidorami przez 5 minut. Podawać od razu.\n\nPrzygotowanie zajmuje 25 minut, przepis na 4 porcje.\n\nCiasto wymaga mąki pszennej, masła, cukru, żółtka i soli. Do sernika potrzebne są mascarpone, twaróg, cukier, jajka, maliny i gorzka czekolada.\n\nProces zaczyna się od wymieszania składników na ciasto i wciśnięcia go w formę do pieczenia na 15 minut w temperaturze 180°C. Następnie łączy się mascarpone z twarogiem i cukrem, a potem dodaje się jajka jeden za drugim. Malinę wmieszać delikatnie, wlać masę na spód i piec przez 45 minut. Po upieczeniu polać wierzch roztopioną czekoladą i całkowicie ostudzić. Całe przygotowanie zajmuje około 90 minut i wystarczy na 8-10 porcji.\n\nDo garnka z rozgrzanym olejem dodaję cebulę i czosnek, smaży się przez 5 minut. Następnie wrzucam marchewkę, ziemniaki i pasternak, mieszam soczewicę z bulionem warzywnym. Dodaję tymianek, kminek i liście laurowe, doprowadzam do wrzenia i gotuje przez 40 minut. Na koniec przyprawiam solą i pieprzem, podaję gorące z chlebem. Danie przygotowuje się w 20 minut, a porcji wychodzi 6.\n\nCzas gotowania to 50 minut. W przepisie na Ciastka Miodowe z Cynamonem łączę miód z masłem, dodaję jajko i wymieszam. W osobnej misce kombinuję mąkę, sodę piekařską, cynamon i goździki, następnie stopniowo wmieszuję do mokrych składników. Do posypania przygotowuję mieszankę cukru i cynamonu.\n\nDla sałatki z burakami i orzechami włoskimi zaczynam od mieszanki zielonych liści, buraka i orzechów, dodaję cienkie plastry czerwonej cebuli. Przygotowuję dressing z octu balsamicznego, oliwy i musztardy dijon, a następnie polewnę sałatkę. Wariant z kozim serem wymaga dodatkowo posiekanych świeżych liści mięty, suszonych żurawinek i plastry jabłka, które układam na wierzchu przed podaniem. cinać kółeczkami, then fill and seal the edges. Cook in salted water until they float to the surface. The recipe yields 30 pierogi and takes about 2 hours total—the dough needs time to rest after kneading, the filling requires sautéing the onions before adding the cabbage and mushrooms with caraway seed and pepper, and finally the pierogi themselves need to be boiled.\n\nFor the risotto, I'm building a creamy spinach dish with garlic as the central flavor. The base uses Arborio rice cooked gradually with warm broth, starting with sautéed onion and garlic in butter and oil, then toasting the rice before deglazing with white wine. Spinach goes in midway through cooking, and Parmesan finishes it with seasoning from nutmeg, salt, and pepper. The garlic variation intensifies this by adding extra minced garlic cloves during the wine reduction step, substituting roasted garlic for fresh, and incorporating roasted garlic cream at the end for a richer, more mellow garlic presence.\n\nFor the Polish compote, this is a traditional summer drink made from raspberries and blackcurrants that balances tartness with sweetness. The key is gentle cooking to preserve the fruit's delicate flavors rather than breaking them down completely. It's versatile enough to serve cold in warm months or heated when it's cold outside, making it a year-round staple in Polish kitchens. Wystarczy około litra kompotu. Przygotowanie zajmuje około 30 minut, a gotowy napój przechowuje się przez tydzień w lodówce.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":10,"cache_creation_input_tokens":20300,"cache_read_input_tokens":84762,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":20300},"output_tokens":3,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"b200fd78-f0e3-4079-b716-02d0c93c8cfb","uuid":"2ff63732-0b5a-4ec0-8a93-ed70b82a22ea"}
